  <description><![CDATA[<p>Maderno has lots of energy. It’s a vibrant town in one of the sunniest spots on <a data-udi="umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473}" title="Lake Garda">Lake Garda</a>. Most of the action is around the beaches – they’re some of the best on the lake. Give some of the water sports a try or just pick out a lounger and chill out on the sand. There’s plenty to do here that’ll keep you active all week. We love the cycling trails that start nearby, or you can grab your boots and go for a stroll around the lake.</p>
<p>The views here are some of our favourite - Mount Pizzocolo dominates the skyline. Pull up a chair at one of the cafés on the promenade and enjoy the views of the yachts. If you want to explore more of the lake, head to the harbour and jump on a ferry. A regular bus service runs along the lake towards <a data-udi="umb://document/8bac09b5ee37405a9498e1494235fa01" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8bac09b5ee37405a9498e1494235fa01}" title="Riva">Riva</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/604dbba59ac64320ab6e9f1e89231a4c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/604dbba59ac64320ab6e9f1e89231a4c}" title="Limone">Limone</a> in the north and <a data-udi="umb://document/e111c61e66e84268913bb65f3bab1c72" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e111c61e66e84268913bb65f3bab1c72}" title="Salo">Salò</a> to the south.</p>]]></description>
