  <thingsToDo><![CDATA[<p style="color: #00533a;"><strong>Walking</strong></p>
<p>There’s lots of varied trails in and around Maderno so you’ll find something to suit all abilities. Some of the woodland tracks around the town have amazing views over the lake and are well worth the effort. The hike up Montemaderno is a great one to do – you can stop for lunch up here and look around the historic centre. If you fancy getting back to nature, then head along Valle delle Cartiere. It’s only a few minutes from the centre of town and the path will take you through the valley past streams, bridges and ruins. Make a day of it by visiting the paper mill museum while you’re nearby.</p>
<p style="color: #00533a;"><strong>Cycling</strong></p>
<p>We can’t resist cycling along the lake when we stay here. The first place we head to is the Valley of the Paper Mills – getting there is easy. Pedal along a nice, flat path and you can visit some lovely little villages that are nearby too. If you want a challenge, head to the mountains behind Maderno. There’s plenty of hair-raising trails to explore and you’ll get some fantastic views of the lake from up here.</p>
<p style="color: #00533a;"><strong>Sightseeing</strong></p>
<p>This area has lots of history and beautiful gardens to explore. Head to the Roman Villa, Paper Mill Museum or the Cathedral, which dates back to the 12th century. The Ghirardi Botanical Gardens are a must-see. They’re over 10,000 square metres with an amazing amount of plants and flowers. It’s a really relaxing place to spend the day. Gardone Riviera is just along the lake and there’s more to explore here, like the famous Vittoriale House &amp; Gardens and Heller Botanical Gardens. Make sure you’re back in Maderno on Thursday though for the weekly market. We love walking around it and soaking up the atmosphere.</p>
<p style="color: #00533a;"><strong>Water based</strong></p>
<p>Maderno has some of Lake Garda’s best beaches so a day by the water is a must. You can grab a lounger and chill on the sand or head into the water for a swim. There’s quite a few water sports here too so you can try a bit of snorkelling or even learn how to sail.</p>]]></thingsToDo>
